        <mxCell id="e_assumptions" parent="1" style="text;html=1;fontSize=11;fontColor=#232F3E;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Assumptions:&#xa;• Tableau Server is assumed already deployed on EC2 within HDB&#39;s VPC (e.g. via AWS Marketplace / Quick Start CloudFormation) — its own install/HA setup is out of scope for this design.&#xa;• Tableau Cloud (SaaS) was not assumed, since it sits outside AWS and would force Athena Driver traffic over the public internet, conflicting with the private-traffic requirement.&#xa;• A VPC Interface Endpoint (AWS PrivateLink) for Athena keeps query traffic within the AWS private network — the Athena public endpoint remains globally reachable but is not used on this path.&#xa;• Only the hashed/ S3 prefix is registered in the Glue Data Catalog (manual DDL, 12 fixed columns, partitioned by month) — raw/cleaned/transformed/failed are not exposed to Athena, since they are not analysis-ready.&#xa;• No crawler used: schema is fixed and already known from the pipeline&#39;s own output structure.&#xa;• Every hop here is a genuine request/response (query, metadata lookup, S3 scan), so each gets a yellow call arrow and a blue data-return arrow." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="1290" x="70" y="680" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
